When people meet my fur kids I am often asked if I picked them based on their color since they all three match. I was awakened by Piko's plaintive cries outside my apartment in Ishiyama, Japan back in 2000. A coworker in Maine in 2002 asked if I would take in a cat her brother found; of course I had to say "yes" when I saw Lucy was a tortie like Piko. I had no intention of adopting a dog when I met @corbinthekelpie @lexingtonhumane while leading some teen volunteers. He had just come down to the adoption floor and was timid and wouldn't come out of his kennel for the kids so I stayed after to work with him and then came early/stayed late following sessions until I couldn't bear the thought of him with anyone other than me. ğŸ˜ And here we are, one big happy family.
